                <h1>How to Easily Fill Backgrounds in Photoshop</h1>
                <p>To fill a background in Photoshop, first, select the layer you want to modify. Next, choose the Paint Bucket Tool from the toolbar. Select your desired color from the color palette. Click on the area to fill. For precise fills, use the Magic Wand or Lasso Tool to create a selection before applying the Paint Bucket. Adjust opacity and blending modes as needed.</p>
